<p itemprop="description">Technical design involves creating detailed specifications and blueprints for technical solutions, defining system components, interfaces, and implementation approaches to meet functional and non-functional requirements.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand technical design principles and recognise the importance of detailed technical design in successful system implementation.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can create basic technical designs, produce technical documentation, and contribute to design reviews and implementation planning.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can create comprehensive technical designs, establish design standards and patterns, and ensure designs meet performance and quality requirements.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can lead technical design strategy, establish design methodologies and frameworks, and mentor others in advanced technical design techniques.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

